item.name: Orders

request.description:
This API will list orders from your Nimbuspost account. You can also sort and filter the data according to your needs by passing the optional parameters. Not passing anything will display the data in the default format.

Parameters:

PARAMS REQUIRED DATA TYPE DESCRIPTION EXAMPLE
page NO integer The page number to display. 5
per_page NO integer The number of entries per page. 5
sort NO string Sort conditions: ASC or DESC ASC
sort_by NO string The Field to sort by: id or status id
to NO string The end date. 2018-07-24
from NO string The start date. 2019-07-24

Get the order details of a particular order through this API by passing the Nimbuspost order id in the endpoint URL itself. Type Nimbuspost Order id in place of {id}. No other body parameters are required.

Parameters:

EXAMPLE
../orders/4433

Use this API to Create custom order in your Nimbuspost account

Parameters:

PARAMS REQUIRED DATA TYPE DESCRIPTION EXAMPLE
order_number YES string The order number generated from your sales channel 4423
payment_method YES string Order Payment Type. Allowed Values: prepaid, COD Prepaid
amount YES integer Calculated sub total amount in Rupee Prepaid
fname YES string First name of the customer Vikalp
lname YES string Last name of the customer Sharma
address YES string Address of the customer House No 11, Pocket 12
address_2 NO string Address 2 of the customer Near Metro Station
phone YES integer 10 Digit mobile number of the customer 9999999999
city YES string City of the customer New Delhi
state YES string state of the customer Delhi
country YES string Country of the customer India
pincode YES integer 6 Digit are pin code of the customer 110022
weight NO integer Total weight of the package (grams) 300
length NO integer Length of the shipment (in cms) 15
height NO integer Height of the shipment (in cms) 15
breadth NO integer Breadth of the shipment (in cms) 15
products[] Yes array name, qty & price array( array( 'name' => 'product name', 'qty' => '5', 'price' => '999 ) )

Use this API to Create and ship custom order using a single API

Parameters:

PARAMS REQUIRED DATA TYPE DESCRIPTION EXAMPLE

item.name: Shipments

request.description:
Use this API to do multiple tasks in one go, namely creating a enw order, request AWB for its shipment. Make sure to create order allocation rules before using this API. Allcoation rules can be set inside Nimbuspost dashboard by visiting Addons->Order allocation engine.

Parameters:

PARAMS REQUIRED DATA TYPE DESCRIPTION EXAMPLE
consignee[name] Yes string Customer Name Vikalp Sharma
consignee[company_name] NO string Customer Company Name (optional) ABC PVT LTD.
consignee[address] Yes string Customer Delivery Address 140, ABC road
consignee[address_2] No string Customer nearby address Near metro station
consignee[city] Yes string Customer city Gurgaon
consignee[state] Yes string Customer state Haryana
consignee[pincode] Yes numbers 6 digit customer pincode 122001
consignee[phone] YES integer 10 Digit mobile number of the customer 9999999999
order[order_number] YES string The order number generated from your sales channel 4423
order[payment_type] YES string Order Payment Type. Allowed Values: prepaid, cod, reverse Prepaid
order[total] YES Float Calculated total amount in Rupee 200
order[shipping_charges] No float Shipping charges for your order (If any) 200
order[cod_charges] No float COD charges for your order (If any) 50
order[discount] No float Discount applied to order (If any) 60
order[package_weight] No integer Package weight (in grams) 500
order[package_length] No integer Package lenght (in cms) 10
order[package_breadth] No integer Package breadth (in cms) 10
order[package_height] No integer Package height (in cms) 10
pickup_warehouse_id YES integer The ID of the warehouse for the pickup. 3
rto_warehouse_id No integer The ID of the warehouse for RTO. 3
courier_id No integer Courier ID. Is mentioned, then AWB will be booked from specific courier company. 3
order_items[] Yes array required: name, qty & price array( array( 'name' => 'product name', 'qty' => '5', 'price' => 999, 'sku' => 'SKU001' ) )
Be sure to input the correct calculated total amount. This is not calculated automatically through the API. Courier ID is optional while making request using this API. If courier ID is passed then system will try to generate AWB using that courier ID. If AWB generation fail because of any reason then order allocaiton engine will choose courier partner as per matchin rule.

sort NO string Sort conditions: ASC or DESC ASC
sort_by NO string The Field to sort by: id or status id
to NO string The end date. 2018-07-24
from NO string The start date. 2019-07-24
